Requirements:
1.  Qt 4.x or later.
    Qt may be downloaded from
    http://trolltech.com/developer/downloads/qt/index.
2.  MySQL 5.0.33 or later, or PostgreSQL 7.4.16 or later.
    MySQL may be downloaded from http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/5.0.html
    and PostgreSQL from http://www.postgresql.org/download.
3.  YAZ 2.1.53 or later.
    YAZ may be downloaded from http://www.indexdata.dk/yaz.
4.  A C++ compiler.

Qt 4.x Preparation (Unix):
1.  Please build Qt with the mysql or postgresql driver, for example:
    ./configure -v -qt-sql-mysql -I /usr/local/include/mysql \
    -L /usr/local/lib/mysql -qt-sql-psql -I /usr/local/include/postgresql \
    -L /usr/local/lib/postgresql
2.  You may also build the drivers as plugins.

MySQL Preparation:
1.  Log into MySQL as an administrator and run the mysql_create_tables.sql
    script.
2.  Create additional users.

PostgreSQL Preparation:
1.  Log into PostgreSQL and run the postgresql_create_tables.sql script.
2.  Create additional users.

Building (Unix):
1.  Set the environment variables LD_LIBRARY_PATH, PATH, QMAKESPEC, and QTDIR
    accordingly.
2.  Update the appropriate project file, if necessary.
3.  Run qmake -o Makefile file.pro.
4.  Run make.

Installing (Unix):
1.  Create the directory /usr/local/biblioteq (/Applications/BiblioteQ.d on
    OS X).
2.  Modify biblioteq.conf and copy it to /usr/local/biblioteq
    (/Applications/BiblioteQ.d on OS X).
3.  Copy BiblioteQ (BiblioteQ.app on OS X) to /usr/local/biblioteq
    (/Applications/BiblioteQ.d on OS X).
4.  Copy icons.d to /usr/local/biblioteq/icons.d
    (/Applications/BiblioteQ.d/icons.d on OS X).
5.  Set the appropriate permissions on the aforementioned files.
